
@startuml
' Define classes

class School {
  -name: String
  -principal: Teacher
}

class Teacher {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -email: String
}

class Student {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -school: School
  -classGroup: ClassGroup
}

class ClassGroup {
  -name: String
  -students: List<Student>
  -classroom: Classroom
}

class Classroom {
  -name: String
  -capacity: Integer
}

class Room {
  -name: String
}

class TeachingAssignment {
  -teacher: Teacher
  -school: School
  -hours: Integer
}

' Define associations and multiplicity

School "1" *-- "1" Teacher : principal
Teacher "0..*" -- "1" School : teaches at
Teacher "1" -- "0..1" TeachingAssignment : has assignment
TeachingAssignment "1" -- "1" School : belongs to
TeachingAssignment "1" -- "1" Teacher : belongs to

Student "1" -- "1" School : attends
Student "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : belongs to

ClassGroup "1" -- "1" Classroom : assigned to
ClassGroup "1" -- "10..31" Student : contains

Room <|-- Classroom
@enduml

### Explanation of Key Relationships:
- `School` has **exactly one principal**, who is a `Teacher`.
- A `Teacher` can teach at **up to three schools**, with each teaching relationship having a number of **hours**.
- A `Student` belongs to **exactly one class group**, which is in **exactly one classroom**.
- `Classroom` inherits from `Room`, but adds **capacity**.
- `Room` is a generalization for both classrooms and other rooms (e.g., gym), which have a **size** instead of capacity.

